covered: Valid Deletion: Multiple scenarios verify account closure semantics across default and various optional-parameter combinations (TC01–TC07, TC11).
Non-Existent Resource: Idempotent behavior tested for non-existent account (TC12).
Concurrency: Tests exercise concurrent/dependent operations and high-load scenarios (TC18, TC07).
gaps: Soft Deletes: No explicit tests asserting whether deletion is soft vs. hard; verification limited to "closed" state.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or rate limiting on DELETE requests.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) on DELETE responses.
recommendations: Add explicit soft-delete semantics tests to confirm whether the account is permanently removed or only marked as closed.
Introduce rate-limiting tests on DELETE to validate robustness under high request rates.
Introduce tests validating caching headers and idempotent behavior across retries.
